-- Lufthansa to Pay All Employees One-Time Bonus of $930 on Earnings Forecast
-- B y   T o m   L a v e l l
-- 2010-12-06T16:12:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/lufthansa-to-pay-all-employees-one-time-bonus-of-930-on-earnings-forecast.html
Deutsche Lufthansa AG will pay
employees a one-time bonus of 700 euros ($930) in January, based
on company earnings projections for 2010, Chief Executive
Officer Wolfgang Mayrhuber said today in a letter to employees.  The payments will be in addition to bonuses specified in
work contracts, Mayrhuber and other management board members
said in the letter obtained by Bloomberg News.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Lavell at 
 tlavell@bloomberg.net  